{"title": "Forsaken Inn", "description": "Told from the perspective of a Mrs. Truax, the owner of an inn during the time of the American and French Revolutions, \"The Forsaken Inn\" is a locked-room mystery that keeps readers guessing about what has happened. A young couple stays at the inn for the night, and goes on their way in the morning ... and several years later, the bride's body is found in a secret room of the inn. Yet, many people saw that bride leave with her husband. How can this be?<br /><br />\n\nGreen tells her tale through Mrs. Truax' diary, and through letters and discussions with other characters who were friends of the young couple. An entertaining and highly recommended read. (Summary by Richard Kilmer)", "duration": 23489, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "407", "name": "Anna Katharine Green"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/theforsakeninn_1404_librivox/forsaken_inn_1404.jpg", "copyright_year": "1889", "genres": ["Crime & Mystery Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Richard Kilmer"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Richard Kilmer"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Barry Eads"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "mim@can (1949-2017)"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Oak Parlor", "readers": [4078], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/theforsakeninn_1404_librivox/forsakeninn_01_green_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1348}, {"section": 2, "title": "Burritt", "readers": [4078], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/theforsakeninn_1404_librivox/forsakeninn_02_green_64kb.mp3", "duration": 837}, {"section": 3, "title": "A Fearful Discovery", "readers": [4078], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/theforsakeninn_1404_librivox/forsakeninn_03_green_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1454}, {"section": 4, "title": "Questions and Answers", "readers": [4078], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/theforsakeninn_1404_librivox/forsakeninn_04_green_64kb.mp3", "duration": 808}, {"section": 5, "title": "Am I